{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Atka Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Atka Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Victoria Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|76|41|S|161|33|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Fry Glacier]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Atka Glacier''' ({{coord|76|41|S|161|33|E|type:glacier_region:AQ_source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is the [[glacier]] immediately east of [[Flagship Mountain]], draining north into [[Fry Glacier]] in [[Victoria Land]]. It was discovered and named in 1957 by the New Zealand Northern Survey Party of the [[Commonwealth Trans-Antarctic Expedition]], 1956&ndash;58, and named after [[USCGC Southwind (WAGB-280)|USS ''Atka'']], an American [[icebreaker]] in the convoy to [[McMurdo Sound]] in the 1956&ndash;57 season.
