{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Deinococcus apachensis'' | image = | image_caption = | regnum = [[Bacterium|Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Deinococcus-Thermus]] | classis = [[Deinococci]] | ordo = [[Deinococcales]] | familia = [[Deinococcaceae]] | genus = ''[[Deinococcus]]'' | species = '''''apachensis''''' | binomial = ''Deinococcus apachensis'' | binomial_authority = Rainey and da Costa 2005 }}
'''''Deinococcus apachensis''''' is a species of [[bacteria]] in the phylum [[Deinococcus-Thermus]]. Strains of this species were isolated from soil samples from [[Arizona]] after exposure to more than 15 [[Gray (unit)|kGy]] of radiation.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Rainey|first1=F. A.|last2=Ray|first2=K.|last3=Ferreira|first3=M.|last4=Gatz|first4=B. Z.|last5=Nobre|first5=M. F.|last6=Bagaley|first6=D.|last7=Rash|first7=B. A.|last8=Park|first8=M.-J.|last9=Earl|first9=A. M.|last10=Shank|first10=N. C.|last11=Small|first11=A. M.|last12=Henk|first12=M. C.|last13=Battista|first13=J. R.|last14=Kampfer|first14=P.|last15=da Costa|first15=M. S.|title=Extensive Diversity of Ionizing-Radiation-Resistant Bacteria Recovered from Sonoran Desert Soil and Description of Nine New Species of the Genus Deinococcus Obtained from a Single Soil Sample|journal=Applied and Environmental Microbiology|date=8 September 2005|volume=71|issue=9|pages=5225–5235|doi=10.1128/AEM.71.9.5225-5235.2005|pmid=16151108|pmc=1214641}}</ref>
